<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-903] Data sources used in DB mediators are closed without considering the fact that the associated datasource is configured globally, while hot-updating a proxy service.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-903</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s assume we have a proxy service that has DBLookup mediator configured to use a globally defined datasources in one of its sequences. There, if we hot update the service, like you mentioned, the existing service is stopped and all the mediator life cycles configured would also be destroyed. When the AbstractDBMediator&apos;s destroy method gets invoked, it closes the associated datasource without considering the fact that it is configured globally. Therefore the subsequent invocations fail as the datasource has already been closed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
